---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="Chrome Web Vitals Extension | Maintained by jmfernxndez"
  description="Discover the Chrome Web Vitals extension, now maintained by jmfernxndez. Optimize your site's Core Web Vitals (LCP, CLS, INP) with this essential tool!"
>
  <div class="container">
    <h1>Chrome Web Vitals Extension: Maintained by jmfernxndez</h1>

    <section class="intro">
      <p>
        The <strong>Chrome Web Vitals extension</strong> is your go-to tool for optimizing
        website performance. After Google retired it in January 2025, I took over
        its maintenance to keep it accessible for developers and businesses. Monitor
        <a href="https://web.dev/vitals/" target="_blank">Core Web Vitals</a
        >—Largest Contentful Paint (LCP), Cumulative Layout Shift (CLS), and
        Interaction to Next Paint (INP)—to boost user experience and SEO.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="features">
      <h2>Why Use the Web Vitals Extension?</h2>
      <p>
        As a freelance web developer, I’ve ensured the Chrome Web Vitals
        extension remains a vital resource for optimizing modern websites. Key
        features include:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Real-Time Metrics</strong>: Track LCP, CLS, and INP directly
          in Chrome for instant performance insights.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>User-Friendly Interface</strong>: Simple, intuitive design for
          developers of all levels.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>SEO Boost</strong>: Improve your site’s Core Web Vitals to
          rank higher on search engines.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Open-Source</strong>: Contribute or explore the code in my <a
            href="https://github.com/jmfernxndez/web-vitals-extension"
            target="_blank">GitHub repository</a
          >.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="why-me">
      <h2>Why Trust My Maintenance?</h2>
      <p>
        With Google no longer supporting the Web Vitals extension, I stepped in
        to keep this critical tool alive. As an experienced freelance web
        developer, I bring:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Technical Expertise</strong>: Skilled in JavaScript, web
          performance optimization, and modern development practices.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Commitment to Quality</strong>: Regular updates to ensure
          compatibility with the latest Chrome versions.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Community Focus</strong>: Actively engaging with user feedback
          to improve the extension.
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        Download the extension from the <a
          href="https://chromewebstore.google.com/detail/illmkcoedmdanbkoihjpipllkaoakccm/"
          target="_blank">Chrome Web Store</a
        > or check out the <a
          href="https://github.com/jmfernxndez/web-vitals-extension"
          target="_blank">source code</a
        > to get started!
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="cta">
      <h2>Optimize Your Site Today</h2>
      <p>
        Ready to enhance your website’s performance? Install the Chrome Web
        Vitals extension or <a href="/contact">contact me</a> for custom web development
        services to take your site to the next level.
      </p>
    </section>
  </div>

  <style>
    .container {
      max-width: 800px;
      margin: 0 auto;
      padding: 2rem;
      font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
    }
    h1 {
      font-size: 2.5rem;
      color: #1a1a1a;
      text-align: center;
      margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    }
    h2 {
      font-size: 1.8rem;
      color: #333;
      margin-top: 2rem;
      margin-bottom: 1rem;
    }
    p {
      line-height: 1.6;
      color: #555;
      margin-bottom: 1rem;
    }
    ul {
      list-style-type: disc;
      margin-left: 2rem;
      margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    }
    li {
      margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
      color: #555;
    }
    a {
      color: #007bff;
      text-decoration: none;
    }
    a:hover {
      text-decoration: underline;
    }
